def: Inclined to exult; characterized by, or expressing, exultation;rejoicing triumphantly.Break away, exultant, from every defilement. I. Tay;or.

Designating, or pertaining to, a certain class of diseases. SeeZymotic disease, below. Zymotic disease (Med.), any epidemic,endemic, contagious, or sporadic affection which is produced by somemorbific principle or organism acting on the system like a ferment.

One of the classes of Mollusca, of great extent. It includesmost of the marine spiral shells, and the land and fresh-watersnails. They generally creep by means of a flat, muscular disk, orfoot, on the ventral side of the body. The head usually bears one ortwo pairs of tentacles. See Mollusca. [Written also Gasteropoda.]
A corruption of God's; -- formerly used in oaths andejaculatory phrases. "Ods bodikin." "Ods pity." Shak.
A cuplike sucker on the feet of certain insects.
Of or pertaining to the trachea; like a trachea.
A small pan with a handle, in which sauce is prepared over afire; a stewpan.
